# SpatialScore — Cursor Rules

Read this file before every phase. It is the law.

## What This Project Is

SpatialScore is a real-time hackathon intelligence platform. CCTV cameras at a venue feed video to a Google Cloud GPU VM. The VM identifies every participant by face, tracks them across cameras, classifies their activity based on what zone they're in and their body pose (49 keypoints), and scores them in real time. Organizers see a CCTV monitoring wall — a grid of live camera feeds where every person is labeled with a bounding box and their name. Click on any person in the video and their score card pops up. Participants never see the system.

1,000 participants. 3 floors. 10-13 cameras. 24-hour hackathon. Single GCP GPU VM. No on-premise hardware beyond cameras and a relay laptop.

## GCP Project (Buildathon)

All cloud provisioning, VM setup, model downloads, and deployment run in this project. Do not create resources in other GCP projects unless the user explicitly says otherwise.

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| **Project ID** | `buildathon-499300` |
| **Project number** | `635695586626` |
| **Owner account** | `bhargavin189@gmail.com` |

Before any `gcloud`, `gsutil`, or GCP Console work:

```bash
gcloud config set account bhargavin189@gmail.com
gcloud config set project buildathon-499300
```

Recommended VM for SpatialScore: **GCE g2-standard-8** with **NVIDIA L4**, Ubuntu 24.04, in a region with L4 quota (e.g. `us-central1`). Use `./scripts/setup_gcp.sh` on the VM after SSH access.

**Phase 1 resource acquisition** (models, Docker images, reference-repo study clones) is executed on the GCP GPU VM via `scripts/setup_gcp.sh` and `scripts/download_models.sh` — not on the venue laptop.

**No third-party API keys required for Phase 1.** HuggingFace InsightFace weights are public. `JWT_SECRET` and `DB_PASSWORD` are generated locally. `GCS_BUCKET` is config-only until Phase 6 backups.


**Person Detection + Pose:** DEIMv2-wholebody49 (ONNX). 49 keypoints per person (17 body + 6 feet + 26 hands). Runs via ONNX Runtime with CUDA. NOT Ultralytics, NOT YOLO. Do not install ultralytics.

**Face Detection:** SCRFD-10G via ONNX Runtime. From InsightFace buffalo_l model pack.

**Face Recognition:** ArcFace-R100 via ONNX Runtime. 512-dim embeddings. From InsightFace buffalo_l model pack.

**Face Matching:** FAISS IndexFlatIP. Cosine similarity on L2-normalized embeddings. Threshold: 0.5.

**CV Toolkit:** Roboflow supervision. Use sv.ByteTrack for tracking, sv.PolygonZone for zone counting, sv.LineZone for entry/exit, sv.HeatMapAnnotator for heatmaps, sv.get_video_frames_generator for RTSP ingestion. Construct sv.Detections manually from DEIMv2 output — do NOT use sv.Detections.from_ultralytics.

**Video Relay:** MediaMTX (bluenviron/mediamtx Docker image). Receives RTMP from venue, re-exposes as local RTSP.

**Backend:** FastAPI. Async everywhere. Uvicorn with 4 workers.

**Database:** PostgreSQL 16 in Docker on the VM. SQLAlchemy 2.0 async with asyncpg driver. Alembic for migrations.

**Cache + Message Queue:** Redis 7 in Docker on the VM. Redis Streams for camera-worker-to-scoring-engine communication. Sorted sets for leaderboard. Hashes for participant state and zone occupancy. No Kafka. No Pub/Sub. No external message broker.

**Frontend:** React 18 + TypeScript + Vite. Tailwind CSS for styling. Recharts for charts. D3.js for heatmap overlay. Zustand for global state. WebSocket (native + reconnecting-websocket) for live updates.

**Auth:** JWT with python-jose. bcrypt via passlib. 24-hour token lifetime.

**Infrastructure:** Single GCE g2-standard-8 VM (NVIDIA L4, 24GB VRAM, 8 vCPU, 32GB RAM). Docker Compose orchestrates everything. Cloud Storage for backups only.

**Inference Runtime:** ONNX Runtime is the ONLY inference runtime. All three models (SCRFD, ArcFace, DEIMv2) run through onnxruntime with CUDAExecutionProvider. No PyTorch at inference time. No TensorFlow. No separate model servers.

## Architecture — The Data Flow

```
Venue cameras (RTSP) → Laptop ffmpeg (RTMP) → MediaMTX on VM (local RTSP)
    → Camera Workers (1 per stream, GPU access)
        → DEIMv2 (person detection + 49 keypoints)
        → SCRFD + ArcFace + FAISS (face identity, every 2 seconds)
        → supervision ByteTrack (tracking)
        → supervision PolygonZone (zone classification)
        → Activity classification (zone + hand position heuristic)
        → Redis Stream: activity events
    → Scoring Engine (consumes Redis Stream)
        → Weighted score calculation
        → Behavioral tag assignment
        → PostgreSQL (permanent storage)
        → Redis (leaderboard, participant state)
        → WebSocket push to dashboard
    → API Server (FastAPI)
        → REST endpoints + WebSocket channels
        → Annotated MJPEG streams for CCTV wall
    → Dashboard (React)
        → CCTV wall: camera grid with labeled bounding boxes
        → Click-to-inspect: score card popup
        → Heatmap, leaderboard, energy graph, alerts
```

